Response for PR #2661444569: The pull request introduces support for multi-character start and end delimiters for templates used with the `StTemplateRenderer`. The changes include updating the `StTemplateRenderer` class to accept strings for delimiters, preprocessing the template to convert custom delimiters to the standard StringTemplate format (`{}`), and updating test cases to reflect the new functionality. The code also includes validation to ensure the delimiters are not null or empty.

The changes appear well-implemented and address the stated goal of allowing more flexible delimiter configurations. The addition of tests covering the new functionality is positive. The code is generally clean and readable.

Approve
