Response for PR #2903282044: The code removes redundant index existence checks in `ElasticsearchVectorStore`’s `doAdd`, `doDelete` (two overloads), and `afterPropertiesSet` methods. This improves performance by avoiding unnecessary HTTP requests. The logic has been adjusted to rely on exception handling during index operations instead of proactively checking for index existence.

The change appears straightforward and addresses the issue described in the pull request description. It simplifies the code and should result in a performance improvement.

Approve
